HEADWORD: Espauliere
<hw>Es`pau`liere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. & F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧pauli⟦egrave⟧re</ets>. See <er>Espalier</er>.]</ety> <def>A
defense for the shoulder, composed of flexible overlapping plates of
metal, used in the 15th century; -- the origin of the modern
<xex>epaulette</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
